-Exhausted Tired Cookies:
-Base Ingredients
270 g all-purpose flour
150 g granulated sugar
165 g packed brown sugar
16 tbsp butter
-Flavor Ingredients
200 g chocolate
2.0 tsp vanilla
---
Instructions
Step 1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.
Step 2: Mix together dry ingredients, combining flour, , in a large bowl. In another bowl, cream together granulated sugar, packed brown sugar and butter, then add vanilla
Step 3: Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing well. Once mixed, add the chocolate.
Step 4: Let the mixture rest for 2 hours in the refrigerator. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add 45 grams of dough, rolled into a sphere. Bake for 10 minutes, turning the sheet around halfway through the baking time.
Step 5: Let the cookies cool.